milestone.title: Bitbucket Data Analysis
milestone.description: Atlassian Bitbucket is an alternative hosting solution to Github. The goal of this data analysis to test conclusions drawn from Github data analysis and to provide additional insight into potential confounding factors that may be influencing Github results. The key challenge here is that a data archive will need to be created from scratch as I was unable to find another archive effort. Additionally, the data available through Bitbucket may not perfectly mirror the Github data. Identifying (and adjusting for) these differences will be required for any comparisons.

issue.title: Add github reporter status_url config option
issue.body:
Make it possible to set the github status link to something other than the
zuul-server status url. This allows the github status to link to the log output
for the jobs. If set, this url will be run through the same formatter
as the url_pattern used for comment links. If unset, it will fall back to the
previous behaviour of using the zuul_server status_url.

Also make the github reporter report() function take the same argument list as
the abstract base class.

Change-Id: I5f2ff35bb38426ddcd7f65798b4f114256a54847

milestone.title: Measuring Value: Bugs
milestone.description: If CI reduces errors in new code, then projects that use CI should have less bugs reported against releases than projects that do not use CI. Therefore, the number of bugs associated with a new release is an effective measurement of CI "value".

issue.title: Update entities for events
issue.body: For events that involve creating or updating Pull Requests or Issues, the original entity needs to be updated. The updated entity will be in the payload so there's no need to make another api call. This should just start out as logic in the script. Eventually we can explore if this could be moved into a trigger on the Events table.
